1.e6 {%02 (The black's queen and rook are under the attack now, so the only real forcing move black has here is Qc5)}
{%03(As usual we should realize all the forcing moves-candidates first. They are:
Qf6, Qh4, Ne6, Nf5, e6. We need to calculate these moves first and only then we
may start to think about the simple moves. The calculation will not be very
long, because most of these moves-candidates are obviously bad. But we need to look quickly at every possibility.)}
( 1.Qxh4 Qxh4 $19 ) ( 1.Qf6+ Qxf6 2.exf6+ Kxf6 {%02 losing a pawn} )
( 1.Ne6+ fxe6 $19 ) ( 1.Nf5+ Nxf5 $19 ) Qxc5 {%02
 (Now white has a choice, so we need to realize the candidate moves again. The
are: Qh4, Nf5, ed. First we should calculate the most forcing move - check. Then captures ed and Qh4)}
2.Nf5+ Qxf5 {%02 (the only move to save the queen)} 3.Qxf5
( 3.exd7 Qxf2 4.d8Q Qxg2# ) Nxf5 4.exd7 {%02 promoting the pawn, so white is winning}
