(It is certainly a tactical position, so we should realize the candidate moves
here. They are: Qd2, e2 (checks), Rc3 (capture).)}
( 1...Qd2+ 2.Qxd2 exd2 3.dxc8Q+ $18 ) 2.Bxe2 {%02 now the moves candidates are Qe2, Qd4, Rc3. First as usual we should calculate checks.}
( 2.Kc2 e1Q+ $19 ) Qd4+ {%02 (now white has a couple of answers: Qd4 (capture), Kc2, Ke1, Qd3, Bd3)}
( 2...Qxe2+ 3.Kxe2 $18 ) 3.Ke1 ( 3.Qxd4 Rc1# ) ( 3.Qd3 Rc1# )
( 3.Kc2 {%02
 (black has several possible moves, but we should not calculate them, because
black is winning after the simple move Rc3. So for now we should stop to
calculate this line. If this position happens in the game - then we will calculate it properly)}
Rxc3+ 4.bxc3 {%02 and at least Qd7 winning} ) ( 3.Bd3 Rxc3 4.Rxh6+
Kg8 {%02 winning} ) Rxc3 {%02 (the only real move candidate)}
4.Rxh6+ {%02 (white also has bc, but we should calculate the most forcing moves first)}
Kg7 5.bxc3 {%02
 and here at least black can play Qd7 winning the game, so we can stop to
calculate this line, because the first move e2 is winning for black and we should do it.}
