1...Bxe3+ {%02 (now white has 3 moves, and we should calculate all of them)}
{%03( Let's think about the opponent's threats first. White is threatening Bf7 and
Qf8 mate. So black need to be careful. The forcing moves-candidates for black
are: Be3, Be6, Bh3. Certainly we should calculate the most forcing move first - Be3)}
2.Bxe3 ( 2.Kg2 Bh3+ 3.Kxh3 Rxd8 $19 ) ( 2.Kh1 {%02 (now black has 2 forcing moves: Bh3 and Be6)}
Bh3 ( 2...Be6 3.Qxa8 Bxd5+ 4.Rf3 Bxf3# ) 3.Bxf7+ {%02 (for an opponent we also should calculate the most forcing moves first)}
Kh8 4.Qxa8 Bxf1 5.Qxf8# ) Qxf1+ {%02 (black has the only forcing move really)}
3.Kxf1 Bh3+ 4.Kf2 Rxd8 $19 {  As you can see with the right way of thinking you can calculate the lines very quickly even in so complicated positions!}
